I got exactly the same problem and fix it.

To avoid this situation， you should add driver name in django database settings. Such as

`DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'NAME': 'xxx',
        'ENGINE': 'sql_server.pyodbc',
        'HOST': r'127.0.0.1',
        'USER': 'sa',
        'PASSWORD': 'xxx',
        'OPTIONS': {
            'driver': 'SQL Server Native Client 10.0'
        },
    },
}`

