@ajkavanagh A fair point. I too thought it was a bit off when I first saw it, since its conflating visibility of endpoints and versions of endpoints.

I'm happy to move the api version context bit into its own VolumeAPIContext. Naturally, we'll also need to update the corresponding charms in [LP #1733566](https://bugs.launchpad.net/charm-nova-compute/+bug/1733566); which I'm also happy to do.

Ideally, this would come along by way of the [service-discovery spec](https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/charm-specs/specs/queens/approved/service-discovery.html) as it seems a natural fit. Yet, progress is seemingly slow or non-existent for the service-discovery work unfortunately.

At Stanford, we use Torque (which itself is flaky), which can be turned on by adding ```"workers": {
        "default_docker_image": "codalab/ubuntu:1.9",
        "shared_file_system": true,
        "torque": {
            "bundle_service_url": "...",
            "log_dir": "...",
            "min_seconds_between_qsub": 10,
            "password_file": "...",
            "ssh_host": "<where to ssh to run job>"
        }
    }
}```
But if you have a different setup, you might have to change the code to make it work.  We might deprecate this stuff anyway, since it's pretty flaky.

I'd probably recommend just running a bunch of `cl-worker` jobs manually on a bunch of your machines.

