They already receive the object being serialized as well as the context. If the expectation of passing a callable to Nested would be to generate a schema every time, Method and Function can do that. It seems like a better fit after thinking it over, at least from my POV.

Basically,

```python
class MySchema(Schema):
     owner = Method('owner_serial', 'owner_deserial')

    def owner_serial(self, value):
        if isinstance(value, User):
            return UserSchema(...).dumps(value)
        else:
            return OtherSchema(...).dumps(value)
```

